content:
The BrowserId_sec Cookie Was Removed

The BrowserId_sec cookie is no longer rendered in Salesforce because the BrowserId cookie serves the same purpose. Also, for clarity, we updated Salesforce Help to reflect where the BrowserId cookie is rendered.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience, Salesforce Classic, and all versions of the Salesforce mobile app in all editions.

Salesforce Help: Salesforce Platform Cookies (can be outdated or unavailable during release preview)
title: BrowserId Sec Cookie Removed
